DISTRIBUTION. Countries by the Persian Gulf—from 
<collectingCountry box="[746,794,1910,1933]" name="Iraq" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[804,889,1909,1934]" name="Kuwait" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[901,1050,1909,1934]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1061,1121,1909,1934]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">UAE</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1132,1203,1909,1934]" name="Oman" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Oman</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1259,1910,1933]" name="Iran" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Iran</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1389,1909,1934]" name="Pakistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,212,1945,1970]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274306" country="Iran" location="Ilam" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Ilam">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[348,404,152,175]" name="Iran" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[418,499,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49. 44" captionStartId="79.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-60@79.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. 44. Hemidactylus flaviviridis. 45. Hemidactylus persicus. 46. Hemidactylus robustus. Question marks indicate dubious data or specimens determined as H. turcicus. 47. Hemidactylus romeshkanicus. 48. Mediodactylus aspratilis. 49. Mediodactylus heterocercum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929730/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
. About 
<quantity box="[586,671,151,176]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="300.0">300 km</quantity>
wide belt along the Persian Gulf coast in 
<collectingRegion box="[1135,1189,151,176]" country="Iran" name="Ilam" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ilam</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1199,1300,152,175]" country="Iran" name="Lorestan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lorestan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1311,1432,151,176]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Khuzestan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,202,188,211]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fars</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[213,309,188,213]" country="Iran" name="Bushehr" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bushehr</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[320,455,188,212]" country="Iran" name="Hormozgan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hormozgan</collectingRegion>
, and Sistan and Baluchistan Prov
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
HABITAT. Inhabits trees, rocks and building wall in xerophytic areas. 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[941,1133,223,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson (1999)</bibRefCitation>
collected his specimens at night on surfaced roads. In 
<collectingCountry box="[457,519,260,285]" name="Qatar" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Qatar</collectingCountry>
found on the ground under wood, rocks and dry leaves (
<bibRefCitation author="Castilla, A. M. &amp; Valdeon, A. &amp; Cogalniceanu, D. &amp; Gosa, A. &amp; Alkuwary, A. &amp; Saifelnasr, E. O. H. &amp; Al Naimi, S. &amp; Al-Hemaidi, A. A. M." box="[1152,1370,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="28" refId="ref48157" refString="Castilla, A. M., Valdeon, A., Cogalniceanu, D., Gosa, A., Alkuwary, A., Saifelnasr, E. O. H., Al Naimi, S. &amp; Al-Hemaidi, A. A. M. (2013) First record of a gecko species to the fauna of Qatar: Hemidactylus persicus Anderson, 1872 (Gekkonidae). QScience Connect, 2013, 28. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5339 / connect. 2013.28" type="journal article" year="2013">
Castilla 
<emphasis box="[1246,1303,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
REMARKS. Deep intraspecific diversification within Iranian specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="1872" box="[991,1120,296,320]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[991,1120,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Carranza, S. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J." box="[1137,1343,295,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="64018" refId="ref65401" refString="Smid, J., Carranza, S., Kratochvil, L., Gvozdik, V., Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J. (2013 a) Out of Arabia: A Complex Biogeographic History of Multiple Vicariance and Dispersal Events in the Gecko Genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). PLoS ONE, 8, e 64018. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0064018" type="journal article" year="2013">
Šmíd 
<emphasis box="[1207,1265,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2013a
</bibRefCitation>
) and its close relation with an unidentified species from NW 
<collectingCountry box="[764,822,332,357]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer, A. M. &amp; Jackman, T. R. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Giri, V. B. &amp; de Silva, A." box="[838,1042,332,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="343 - 352" refId="ref46907" refString="Bauer, A. M., Jackman, T. R., Greenbaum, E., Giri, V. B. &amp; de Silva, A. (2010) South Asia supports a major endemic radiation of Hemidactylus geckos. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 57, 343 - 352. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2010.06.014" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bauer 
<emphasis box="[916,975,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
) indicate that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="1872" box="[1209,1339,333,356]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1209,1339,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a complex of several cryptic species that needs to be revised with material from other parts of the species’ distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
